description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Sister / Senior Charge Nurse - Neonatal ICU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Division: Planned Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Care Group: Women &amp; Children&#39;s&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band: 7&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Salary:£38,890 - £44,503 per annum/pro rata&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: Monday 14th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note that any applicants who hold a Specialist Neonatal Qualification will also receive an RNR payment of £1500 per annum/pro rata&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting for a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Sister / Senior Charge Nurse&lt;/strong&gt; who shares our ambition and vision to deliver the &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Best of Care by the Best People&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; and has the drive to take us forward, by ensuring that the Trust continues to be the first choice for patients and our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Senior Sister / Senior Charge Nurse will work in partnership with a team of highly skilled Consultants and Neonatal Nurse Practitioners who work collaboratively to deliver high quality care to our small patients and their families. We also have close links with Kings College Hospital who provide surgical input for our babies when required. The Kent part of the transport services for London, Kent, Surrey and Sussex is also based with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our level three unit currently has capacity for 12 intensive/high dependency cots and 16 special care cots. We also have a transitional care unit which can accommodate up to eight babies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful post holder will be expected to have proven clinical and managerial experience, effective communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition, you will need to have the ability to provide direction and give inspirational leadership to all members of the multi professional team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position offers a recruitment and retention bonus of £1500 per year to staff with the specialist neonatal qualification (paid monthly in 12 divided payments).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust and its employees are all committed to creating and maintaining a fair and supportive working environment and culture.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of our commitment to you, we will give you the opportunity to utilise and enhance your talents to assist us in the development of shaping the future of Medway NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust offers a number of apprenticeships and training opportunities in Leadership and Management, Business Services, Finance, Accounting, Human Resources, Clinical Support Work, Research and Innovation, Nursing Associate and Assistant Practitioner alongside our in-house comprehensive clinical pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our hope is that our education pathways will play a key role in enabling you to challenge the practices of the past and build capability for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Trust is committed to the protection of children, young people, their families and vulnerable adults accessing its services. Promoting the message that “safeguarding is everyone’s business” is vital to ensure our patients are protected and safe from abuse. To this end you must comply with Trust’s and the Kent and Medway Safeguarding Board’s policies on safeguarding children, young people and vulnerable adults.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our values are &lt;strong&gt;B&lt;/strong&gt;old, &lt;strong&gt;E&lt;/strong&gt;very Person Counts, &lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt;haring and Open and &lt;strong&gt;T&lt;/strong&gt;ogether.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To contribute to our exciting future and become part of our team, apply today.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Anna Francis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Matron - NICU&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;annafrancis@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
